'''[[Afghanistan]]''' competed at the [[Deaflympics]] for the first time during the [[2017 Summer Deaflympics]] which was held in [[Samsun]],[[Turkey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/countries.asp?country=afg|title=Countries {{!}} Deaflympics|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-21}}</ref> Afghani team sent a five-member delegation for the Deaflympic event held in 2017, which is the only Deaflympic event where Afghanistan took part. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deaflympics.com/games.asp?2017/afg|title=Afghanistan {{!}} 2017 Summer Deaflympics|last=|first=|date=|website=www.deaflympics.com|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-09-21}}</ref> The five members were: Ahmad Reshad Azizi ([[400m]])<ref name="Aziziafghanistan">{{cite web |title=Ahmad Reshad Azizi |url=http://www.deaflympics.com/athletes/MmUrYWJMdzJLNFZJUEFENzltOXZRZz09 |website=Deaflympics.com |publisher=International Olympics Committee |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>, Faiz Ahmad Faizi ([[Taekwondo]] -68kg)<ref name="FaizDeaflympics">{{cite web |title=Faiz Ahmad Faiz |url=http://www.deaflympics.com/athletes/NXVpUndlWEIvdklQWDJYUHdtOXNyQT09 |website=Deaflympics.com |publisher=International Olympics Committee |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>, Ekilil Khaliqyar ([[200m]])<ref name="KhaliqyarDeaflympics">{{cite web |title=Eklil Khaliqyar |url=http://www.deaflympics.com/athletes/OXJ6eXNTVXFiZ1p6QjlkZ2pGeTdaZz09 |website=Deaflympics.com |publisher=International Olympics Committee |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>, Payman Noori ([[100m]])<ref name="NooriDeaflympics">{{cite web |title=Payman Noori |url=www.deaflympics.com/athletes/OXJ6eXNTVXFiZ1p6QjlkZ2pGeTdaZz09 |website=Deaflympics.com |publisher=International Olympics Committee |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref> and Ahman Fawad Sultani ([[100m]])<ref name="SultaniDeaflympics">{{cite web |title=Ahmad Fawad Sultani |url=http://www.deaflympics.com/athletes/aUd0WHRUelNMWmtiaXBURy9hTkE0QT09 |website=Deaflympics.com |publisher=International Olympics Committee |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>.<ref name="DeaflympicsAfghanistan">{{cite web |title=Samsun 2017 Afghanistan |url=http://www.deaflympics.com/games/2017-s/AFG |website=deaflympics.com |publisher=International Olympics Committee |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref> Afghanistan is yet to earn a medal at the Deaflympics.
