{{Use Indian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox organization | image = | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | motto = | formation = 1971 | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = <!-- GO, NGO, IGO, INGO, etc --> | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = <!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> | headquarters = | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | language = <!-- official languages --> | leader_title = <!-- position title for the leader of the org --> | leader_name = <!-- name of leader --> | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | remarks = | name = Central Council of Indian Medicine | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200 --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 200px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | abbreviation = CCIM | location = [[New Delhi]] | region_served = [[India]] | membership = | parent_organisation = [[AYUSH|Ministry of Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homoeopathy]] ([[AYUSH]]), | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = [http://www.ccimindia.org/ CCIM] | President = Dr.Vanitha R. }}
'''Central Council of Indian Medicine''' ('''CCIM''') is a statutory body under [[AYUSH|Department of Ayurveda, Yoga and Naturopathy, Unani, Siddha and Homoeopathy]] ([[AYUSH]]), [[Ministry of Health and Family Welfare]], [[Government of India]], set up in 1971 under the [[List of Indian federal legislation#1951.E2.80.931975|Indian Medicine Central Council Act, (Act 48)]] which was passed in 1970. It is one of the [[University Grants Commission (India)#Professional councils|Professional councils]] under [[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Commission]] (UGC) to monitor higher education in Indian systems of medicine, including [[Ayurveda]], [[Siddha]] and [[Unani]].<ref name="About CCIM">[http://ccimindia.org/index.html CCIM website] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226063741/http://ccimindia.org/index.html |date=26 February 2011 }}, retrieved on 15 January 2010</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.education.nic.in/higedu.asp |title=Higher education in India |publisher=Department of Higher Education, [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]], [[Government of India]] |accessdate=2009-11-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091216122916/http://www.education.nic.in/higedu.asp |archivedate=16 December 2009 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=ug>{{cite web |title=Professional Councils |url=http://www.ugc.ac.in/inside/pcouncil.html |date= |publisher='[[University Grants Commission (India)|University Grants Commission]]' (UGC) website|page=}}</ref>
==Overview== It is located in New Delhi, India.<ref name="DAVP">[http://www.davp.nic.in/WriteReadData/ADS/eng_17204_5_0910b.pdf CCIM] DAVP, Department of Advertising, Government of India gazzette, retrieved on 15 January 2010</ref> CCIM was set up to suggest the benchmarks and practices to be followed in Indian medicinal systems.<ref name=CCIM/> CCIM has also been involved in regulating the [[Ayurveda]], [[Siddha]] and [[Unani]] Tibb education courses at the graduate and post-graduate streams.<ref name=CCIM>[http://www.indiaeducationdiary.in/Statutory-Bodies/CCIM/index.asp Central Council for Indian Medicine (CCIM)] India Educationary Website, retrieved on 15 January 2010.</ref> The Siddha course recognition system of CCIM was questioned through a public interest litigation <ref>{{cite news |title=PIL petition questions validity of diploma course in Siddha medicine |url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/09/01/stories/2007090161251000.htm |publisher=[[The Hindu]] |date= 1 September 2007 }}</ref>
