{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = Professor | name = | honorific_suffix = [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics|FInstP]], [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics and Engineering in Medicine|FIPEM]] | image = EWS28.01 - Professor John Clifton and Professor David Delpy.jpg | caption = Clifton (left) with David Delpy | birth_name = John Stephen Clifton | birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1930}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | monuments = | residence = | nationality = [[British people|United Kingdom]] | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Southampton]] | occupation = [[Medical physicist]] | employer = {{Plainlist| * [[Royal South Hants Hospital]] * [[University College Hospital Medical School]] * [[University College London]] * [[University of London]] }} | organization = | agent = | home_town = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = }}
Professor '''John Stephen Clifton''' [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics|FInstP]], [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics and Engineering in Medicine|FIPEM]] (born 1930) is a British [[medical physicist]].
Clifton studied at the [[University of Southampton]], graduating in 1955 and then worked at the [[Royal South Hants Hospital]].<ref name="HoMBRG">{{cite Q|Q29581744}}</ref>
In 1957 he obtained a position at [[University College Hospital Medical School]] becoming head of the medical physics department in 1962.<ref name="HoMBRG" /> The school merged with [[University College London]] and he became Professor of Medical Physics.<ref name="HoMBRG" /> In 1990, he was appointed Joel Professor of Physics Applied to Medicine at the [[University of London]] in 1990, becoming Emeritus upon retirement.<ref name="HoMBRG" />
He served as president of the Hospital Physicists' Association (now the [[Institute of Physics and Engineering in Medicine]]) from 1976 to 1978, and as honorary editor of "[[Physics in Medicine and Biology]]" from 1979 to 1983.<ref name="HoMBRG" /> He was the founding President of the [[European Federation of Organizations for Medical Physics]] from 1980 to 1984, having proposed its establishment in 1978.<ref name="HoMBRG" /> He is a [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics]] (FInstP), and a [[Fellow of the Institute of Physics and Engineering in Medicine]] (FIPEM).<ref name="HoMBRG" />
The John Clifton Prize, initiated in 2011, is awarded by University College London "for the most outstanding performance by a non-final-year undergraduate", in his honour.<ref name="JCP">{{cite web |url=http://www.ucl.ac.uk/medphys/prizes/john-clifton-prize |accessdate=22 June 2017 |title=John Clifton Prize |publisher=[[University College London]] |archiveurl=http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:phJMQ25nD3kJ:www.ucl.ac.uk/medphys/prizes/john-clifton-prize+&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk&client=firefox-b-ab |archivedate=24 May 2017}}</ref>
