The '''Penske workplace shootings''' occurred on January 12, 2010. Three people were killed and two others critically injured in a workplace shooting at a truck rental business located near the city of [[Kennesaw, Georgia]]. The fourth victim later died in 2013 from complications of his injuries. The alleged shooter, Jesse J. Warren, was captured and arrested in the incident.
==Shooting== The shooter, Jesse James Warren, a former employee, walked into the [[Penske Corporation|Penske]] truck rental business Tuesday afternoon wearing [[camouflage]]. He opened fire, shooting five. Four victims were employees, another was a customer. One victim, Van Springer, died at the scene. The other four victims were transported in critical condition to a local hospital. A customer died at the hospital, while Roberto Gonzalez, an employee, died the next day, which brought the death toll to three. Joshua Holbrook and Zach Werner were shot multiple times, but survived Zach later died from complications.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsatlanta.com/news/22232392/detail.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-01-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117010649/http://www.cbsatlanta.com/news/22232392/detail.html |archivedate=2010-01-17 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Penske shooting victim wants control of his life {{!}} 11alive.com|url = http://archive.11alive.com/news/article/256229/40/Penske-shooting-victim-wants-control-of-his-life?fullsite=true|website = 11alive.com|accessdate = 2015-10-19}}</ref> Warren was arrested less than a mile away after he left in a red [[Chevrolet S-10]] truck.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ajc.com/news/news/local/5-shot-2-killed-former-penske-employee-in-custody/nQbfS/|title=5 shot, 2 killed; former Penske employee in custody|work=ajc.com|accessdate=19 October 2015}}</ref>
Warren was declared incompetent to stand trial, and was indefinitely committed to a mental institution in 2017.<ref>https://www.mdjonline.com/news/accused-kennesaw-penske-shooter-jesse-james-warren-sent-to-mental/article_2060894c-76e5-11e7-ac5a-5b21a4bf52ff.html</ref>
