[[Image:Rauchen Verboten.svg|100px|right]] '''Smoking in Colombia''' was [[Smoking ban|banned]] in May 2008 in [[public transport]] vehicles, [[hospital]]s, [[kindergarten]]s and [[school]]s, [[Bar (establishment)|bars]], clubs, [[restaurant]]s, business centers and [[airport]]s.<ref name="tobacco.org 266317"> {{cite web | url= http://www.tobacco.org/news/266317.html | title= Stricter smoking ban takes effect in Colombia | publisher= Tobacco.org | date= 2008-06-02 | accessdate = 2010-09-01 }} </ref> Smoking areas in enclosed public places were also banned.<ref name="tobacco.org 266317" /> ==Prevalence== There are over 5 million smokers in Colombia. Teenage smokers account for nearly a third of smokers, and their numbers continue to rise.<ref name="xinhuanet 8301683" /> The ministry of social security and health reported that diseases related to smoking killed an average of 68 [[Colombian people|Colombians]] per day before the implementation of the ban.<ref name="xinhuanet 8301683"> {{cite news | url= http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-06/02/content_8301683.htm | title= Stricter smoking ban takes effect in Colombia | publisher= [[Xinhua News Agency]] | date= 2008-06-02 | accessdate = 2010-09-01 }} </ref>
